tags.description: National Historic Landmark home of John Jay. Historic Site and Park. Member Site of New York State's Path Through History, Hudson River Valley National Heritage Area and Westchester County African American Heritage Trail. Hours Wed. thru Fri. 10am - 4pm

tags.description: 23-acre park and historic site with 3 owners: the nonprofit Jay Heritage Center(JHC) (1.5 acres), NY State Parks and Westchester County Parks (21.5 acres tenants in common, NY State 90% and Westchester County 10% interest. Operated by JHC for the public.
